   "source": [
    "Connecting to a remote server\n",
    "=============================\n",
    "\n",
    "This example demonstrates how to connect to a remote FusionSC server. Please see the server example to check how to run the corresponding server program."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "ecbd8db0-1cb6-4399-83b4-2dbc80604faf",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import fusionsc as fsc\n",
    "from fusionsc.devices import w7x"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "cf7cf252-ec78-4a6d-8d25-ba691fcb1138",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "backend = fsc.remote.connect(\"http://localhost:12345\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "578b9528-4c4e-4dfc-aca8-707af192a405",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fsc.backends.alwaysUseBackend(backend)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "4548fabe-d21f-466b-a236-00772b70a20b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "phiPlanes = np.linspace(0, 2 / 5 * np.pi, 6, endpoint = False)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Put more starting points inside the island\n",
    "rStart = np.concatenate([\n",
    "    np.linspace(4.5, 4.8, 10, endpoint = False),\n",
    "    np.linspace(4.8, 5.4, 10)\n",
    "])\n",
    "phiStart = np.linspace(0, 2 * np.pi, 5, endpoint = False) + np.pi\n",
    "\n",
    "# Starting on an r, phi grid allows us to see all 5 islands\n",
    "rStartG, phiStartG = np.meshgrid(rStart, phiStart, indexing = 'ij')\n",
    "\n",
    "xStart = rStartG * np.cos(phiStartG)\n",
    "yStart = rStartG * np.sin(phiStartG)\n",
    "zStart = 0 * rStartG\n",
    "\n",
    "startPoints = [xStart, yStart, zStart]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "a366e732-593d-40ee-a3a6-d65c4fa44f3c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "field = w7x.standard()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Let's cheapen our calculation a bit for demonstration\n",
    "grid = w7x.defaultGrid()\n",
    "grid.nR = 64\n",
    "grid.nZ = 64\n",
    "grid.nPhi = 32"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "0cd0ccea-6915-44e2-9ae2-da35175b8f7c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pcPoints = fsc.flt.poincareInPhiPlanes(\n",
    "    startPoints, field, phiPlanes, 200,\n",
    "    grid = grid,\n",
    "    distanceLimit = 1e3, targetError = 1e-3\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "63b6a965-0049-40a1-ad11-b7b9621b28a4",

   ],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "matplotlib.rcParams.update({'font.size': 22})\n",
    "\n",
    "geometry = w7x.op21Geometry().merge()\n",
    "\n",
    "for iPhi, phi in enumerate(phiPlanes):\n",
    "    x, y, z, cLenF, cLenB = pcPoints[:, iPhi, :, :].reshape([5, -1])\n",
    "    r = np.sqrt(x**2 + y**2)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Negative connection lengths indicate that the line segment going through\n",
    "    # the point in that direction is not terminated by collision (e.g. it left\n",
    "    # the grid or hit the distance limit)\n",
    "    mask = np.logical_and(cLenF > 0, cLenB > 0)\n",
    "    mask2 = np.logical_and(cLenF < 0, cLenB < 0)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    cLen = cLenF + cLenB\n",
    "    \n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize = (7, 9))\n",
    "    plt.title(str(np.degrees(phi)) + ' deg.')\n",
    "    #plt.scatter(r[mask], z[mask], c = cLen[mask], norm = matplotlib.colors.LogNorm(), s = 1)\n",
    "    #plt.colorbar(label = 'Connection length [m]')\n",
    "    plt.scatter(r[mask2], z[mask2], c = 'k', s = 0.5)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    geometry.plotCut(phi, edgecolors = 'k')\n",
    "    plt.axis('equal')"
   ]
  },
